scope.summary:
GOAL: Allow any pane in the split layout to be "popped out" into its own OS-native window, and merged back into the main layout. While popped out, the pane's state remains in the shared `PaneRegistry` (it is not removed — only its render destination changes). Merge-back removes the detached window and restores the pane's content to the main split. Expected diff shape: one new file `src/frontend/shell/popout_window.rs` (~250–350 lines), edits to `src/frontend/shell/app.rs` (pop-out tracking state + merge-back logic), and edits to `src/frontend/shell/split_layout.rs` (render a placeholder tile when a pane is popped out).

FILES TO CREATE/EDIT:
- CREATE: `src/frontend/shell/popout_window.rs` — `PopOutState`, `PopOutManager`, `PopOutWindowHost`.
- EDIT: `src/frontend/shell/mod.rs` — add `pub mod popout_window;`.
- EDIT: `src/frontend/shell/app.rs` — add `popout_manager: PopOutManager` to `HandshakeApp`; in `update()`, iterate over active pop-outs and call their render; add pop-out and merge-back actions.
- EDIT: `src/frontend/shell/split_layout.rs` — when a pane is popped out, render a `PopOutPlaceholder` tile showing the pane_type label and a "Merge Back" button.

CORE TYPES:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct PopOutGeometry {
    pub pos: egui::Pos2,   // top-left of the detached window on screen
    pub size: egui::Vec2,  // size of the detached window
}

#[derive(Debug)]
pub struct PopOutState {
    pub pane_id: PaneId,
    pub viewport_id: egui::ViewportId, // egui's deferred viewport id for this pop-out
    pub geometry: PopOutGeometry,
    pub open: bool, // false = merge-back requested this frame
}

pub struct PopOutManager {
    pop_outs: HashMap<PaneId, PopOutState>,
}
```

STEP-BY-STEP IMPLEMENTATION:
1. Define types above in `popout_window.rs`.
2. Implement `PopOutManager::new() -> Self`.
3. Implement `PopOutManager::pop_out(pane_id: PaneId, initial_geometry: PopOutGeometry)` — creates a `PopOutState` with a fresh `egui::ViewportId::from_hash_of(&pane_id)`. Inserts into `pop_outs`. Does NOT remove the pane from the registry.
4. Implement `PopOutManager::merge_back(pane_id: &PaneId)` — sets `pop_outs[pane_id].open = false`.
5. Implement `PopOutManager::is_popped_out(pane_id: &PaneId) -> bool`.
6. Implement `PopOutManager::show_all(ctx, registry, tab_bar_states, factories)` — for each `PopOutState` with `open == true`, call:
   ```rust
   ctx.show_viewport_deferred(
       state.viewport_id,
       egui::ViewportBuilder::default()
           .with_title(format!("Handshake – {}", pane_type_label))
           .with_position(state.geometry.pos)
           .with_inner_size(state.geometry.size)
           .with_close_button(true),
       move |ctx, class| {
           if class == egui::ViewportClass::Deferred {
               egui::CentralPanel::default().show(ctx, |ui| {
                   // render the tab bar for this pane
                   // render the pane content via its factory
               });
               // detect close button: if ctx.input(|i| i.viewport().close_requested())
               // -> set open = false (merge-back)
           }
       }
   );
   ```
7. After `show_all()`, collect all `PopOutState` entries where `open == false` and remove them (drain). This is the merge-back: the pane is already in the registry; the split layout's placeholder tile will automatically disappear next frame because `is_popped_out()` returns false.
8. In `split_layout.rs`, when rendering a pane rect: if `popout_manager.is_popped_out(&pane_id)`, render a `PopOutPlaceholder` instead of the pane content:
   ```rust
   ui.allocate_ui_at_rect(pane_rect, |ui| {
       ui.centered_and_justified(|ui| {
           ui.label(format!("{} (popped out)", pane_label));
           if ui.button("Merge Back").clicked() {
               // set pop_out_merge_request = Some(pane_id)
           }
       });
   });
   ```
9. Pop-out trigger: add `pop_out_request: Option<PaneId>` to `HandshakeApp`. In the pane header or tab bar context menu stub (MT-019), clicking "Pop Out" sets this. In `HandshakeApp::update()`, if `pop_out_request` is Some, call `popout_manager.pop_out(pane_id, PopOutGeometry { pos: cursor_pos, size: Vec2::new(800.0, 600.0) })`.
10. AccessKit for detached windows: each deferred viewport gets its own AccessKit tree. The root node of the detached viewport window has role `Window`, author_id `"popout-window-{pane_id}"`. The pane content nodes inside it retain their existing author_ids (the registry's AccessKit ids are unchanged; only the render host changes).
11. The "Merge Back" button in the placeholder tile: role `Button`, author_id `"merge-back-{pane_id}"`.
12. Geometry persistence: `PopOutGeometry` derives `Serialize`/`Deserialize`. MT-009 includes pop-out geometries in the layout snapshot so windows reopen in the same position after restart.

DEPENDENCIES / UNBLOCK CONDITIONS:
- MT-005 (`PaneRegistry`), MT-006 (split layout), MT-007 (tab bars) must be complete.
- Requires egui 0.29+ `show_viewport_deferred` API. This is the native egui multi-window mechanism; no external windowing library needed.
- On Windows, `eframe` with the `wgpu` backend supports deferred viewports. Confirm this is enabled in `eframe::NativeOptions` in `app.rs`.

RISK IF MISSED:
- Without pop-out support, power users and swarm agents cannot detach a pane to a separate monitor. Without merge-back, detached panes become permanently detached and the layout snapshot is corrupted on restore.
